---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Refund Policy | The Candle Sleeves"
  description="Refund Policy for The Candle Sleeves — our policy on defective products, reprints, cancellations, and customer satisfaction guarantees."
  canonical="https://thecandlesleeves.com/refund-policy"
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: May 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <p>At The Candle Sleeves, we are committed to your satisfaction. Because all products are custom-manufactured to your exact specifications, our refund and return process is different from standard retail. Please read this policy carefully.</p>

      <h2>1. Custom Product Policy</h2>
      <p>All candle sleeves produced by The Candle Sleeves are made-to-order based on specifications and artwork approved by the customer. For this reason, <strong>we do not accept returns or issue refunds for change of mind</strong> or for products that match the approved artwork proof and specifications.</p>
      <p>This policy exists because custom packaging cannot be restocked or resold. We encourage all customers to carefully review digital proofs before approval to ensure the design, dimensions, and specifications are exactly as required.</p>

      <h2>2. Defective or Incorrect Products</h2>
      <p>We stand behind the quality of our work. If your order arrives with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Manufacturing defects (structural failures, poor adhesion, die-cut errors)</li>
        <li>Significant color deviations from the approved proof</li>
        <li>Incorrect quantities (short shipment)</li>
        <li>Wrong product or specifications compared to the confirmed order</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Please notify us within <strong>7 calendar days of delivery</strong> by emailing Info@thecandlesleeves.com with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your order number</li>
        <li>Clear photographs showing the issue</li>
        <li>A written description of the problem</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will review your claim and respond within 3 business days. Valid claims will be resolved through a reprint, partial credit, or full credit/refund, at our discretion.</p>

      <h2>3. Approval Responsibility</h2>
      <p>By approving a digital proof in writing, you confirm that all elements — including text, dimensions, colors, die-cut shape, and branding — are correct. The Candle Sleeves is not responsible for errors that were present in the approved proof, including but not limited to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Spelling or typographical errors</li>
        <li>Incorrect dimensions or measurements provided by the customer</li>
        <li>Design elements that appeared correctly in the approved proof</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Please take time to verify all details thoroughly before approving artwork.</p>

      <h2>4. Order Cancellations</h2>
      <p>Cancellations are accepted under the following conditions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Before artwork approval:</strong> Full deposit refund, minus any incurred design or consultation fees.</li>
        <li><strong>After artwork approval but before production begins:</strong> Partial deposit refund. Design and setup costs will be deducted.</li>
        <li><strong>After production has begun:</strong> No refund is available. All production costs are incurred at this stage.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Cancellation requests must be submitted in writing to Info@thecandlesleeves.com. Verbal cancellations are not accepted.</p>

      <h2>5. Shipping Damage</h2>
      <p>Damage incurred during transit is handled separately from our refund policy. If your order arrives damaged, please refer to our <a href="/shipping-policy">Shipping Policy</a> for instructions on reporting carrier damage. We will assist in filing a claim with the carrier and work toward an appropriate resolution.</p>

      <h2>6. Color Variation Notice</h2>
      <p>Minor color variations between the approved digital proof and the final printed product are inherent in the commercial printing process and do not constitute a defect. This is due to differences in screen display calibration versus physical print output, ink absorption in different paper stocks, and normal print run variation. We work diligently to minimize these variations but cannot guarantee an exact match between screen and print.</p>

      <h2>7. Quantity Tolerances</h2>
      <p>Due to the nature of manufacturing, delivered quantities may vary by up to ±5% from the ordered quantity. This is standard industry practice. In the event of a significant shortfall, we will ship the remaining units or issue a credit for the unfulfilled portion.</p>

      <h2>8. How to Request a Refund or Reprint</h2>
      <p>To initiate a claim, contact us within 7 days of delivery:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:Info@thecandlesleeves.com">Info@thecandlesleeves.com</a> — Subject line: "Order Issue – [Your Order Number]"</li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (503) 358-0443 (follow up in writing for documentation purposes)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Claims submitted after 7 days of delivery will be assessed at our discretion and may not be eligible for resolution.</p>

      <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Refund Policy, please reach out:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:Info@thecandlesleeves.com">Info@thecandlesleeves.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (503) 358-0443</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> 2975 Coburn Hollow Road, Bloomington, IL 61701</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
